p.subtitle
  ' This service tells you if you might be able to get legal aid
  | in England and Wales - and suggests other sources of help if you can’t.

p Don’t use this service if you’ve been charged with a crime.

markdown:
  ### Before you start

  To use this service, you’ll need:

  * last month’s payslips (if you’re working)
  * last month’s  bank statements
  * details of any benefits you got last month

p.action
  button.button.button-get-started ui-sref="checker({ stage: 'problem' })" Start
  small style="display: block" If you might be able to get legal aid, you can speak to an operator about your problem at the end of this service.


markdown:
  ### What is legal aid?

  * it can help you cover the cost of legal advice
  * it can get someone to speak for you in court
  * it can help you resolve family problems without going to court

  ### Who can get legal aid?

  You (and your partner if you have one) must meet BOTH of the following conditions:

  * you must have less than £2,657 a month coming in before tax
  * you must have less than £8,000 in savings or in a home you own
